messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /api/products/{id}

All methods acceptable?
- allMethods: false

Individual methods (based on the code)
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: true
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation
- server.js mounts the product routes with app.use('/api/products', productRoutes); so the router paths defined in routes/productRoutes.js are prefixed with /api/products.
- In routes/productRoutes.js the route for the resource id is defined as router.route('/:id') with handlers:
  - .get(checkObjectId, getProductById)
  - .put(protect, admin, checkObjectId, updateProduct)
  - .delete(protect, admin, checkObjectId, deleteProduct)
  These correspond to GET, PUT and DELETE on /api/products/:id (reported as /api/products/{id}).
- There is no explicit HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE or PATCH handler registered for /:id in the code. Per your instruction to base acceptability on the code (not on implicit framework behaviors), HEAD is marked false even though many frameworks implicitly handle HEAD when GET is present.
- POST is registered for other paths (POST /api/products and POST /api/products/:id/reviews) but not for /api/products/:id, so POST is false for the /api/products/{id} endpoint.
- Therefore only GET, PUT and DELETE are acceptable per the source.
